Steve Brinich (steve-b@access.digex.com) wrote:
:   A few possibilities to improve this would be using something besides the
: usual single space between words (especially if you didn't just use the
:

Dictionary attack are pre-programmed to automagically
find normal words with all possible 1 char errors
(including deletions and additions), all possible 2 char errors,
etc.  Although this adds to the search space the cartesian
product is not nearly as great as simply adding another
word from a collegiate-size dictionary.

Since the "random error" makes it much harder to remember
than adding the extra word, I think you'll benefit much
more by not bothering with the error.

G.
 
